                                                  Problem

                                                  Nitrite is commonly determined by a colorimetric procedure using a reaction called the Griess reaction. In this reaction, the sample containing nitrite is reacted with sulfanilimide and N-(1-Napthyl)ethylenediamine to form a species that absorbs at 550 nm. Using an automated flow analysis instrument, the following results were obtained for standard solutions of nitrite and for a sample containing an unknown amount.

                                                  (a) Obtain the slope and intercept of the calibration curve, and the standard error in y.

                                                  (b) Construct a plot of the calibration curve.

                                                  (c) Determine the concentration of nitrite in the sample and its standard deviation.
